---
---

<section id="how-it-works" class="py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 bg-[#1c1c27]">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-4">
        How it works
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] max-w-xl mx-auto">Three stages. Each mirrors how your own brain handles memory.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="relative">
      <div
        class="hidden lg:block absolute top-14 left-[16.67%] right-[16.67%] h-px border-t-2 border-dashed border-[#2a2a3d]"
        aria-hidden="true"
      ></div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12 lg:gap-8">

        <!-- Step 1: Encoding -->
        <article class="relative flex flex-col items-center lg:items-start text-center lg:text-left">
          <div
            class="relative z-10 w-12 h-12 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-black text-[#13131a] mb-6"
            style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #67e8f9 0%, #a78bfa 100%); box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(103,232,249,0.4);"
          >01</div>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-[#67e8f9] mb-2">Encoding · like the hippocampus</span>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Drop your files. Nothing leaves your device. Knowledge gets encrypted.</h3>
          <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Drag in documents, PDFs, notes, or web clips. Graphnosis reads them locally, extracts entities and relationships, and indexes them into an encrypted binary <code class="text-[#67e8f9] font-mono">.gai</code> file — a knowledge graph your AI can reason over deterministically.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed font-medium">
            No AI API is called during ingest. The indexing cost is $0.
          </p>
          <a href="/reference/file-formats" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-[#67e8f9] hover:underline font-mono mt-1">
            About the .gai format ↗
          </a>
        </article>

        <!-- Step 2: Recall -->
        <article class="relative flex flex-col items-center lg:items-start text-center lg:text-left">
          <div
            class="relative z-10 w-12 h-12 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-black text-[#13131a] mb-6"
            style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #67e8f9 0%, #a78bfa 100%); box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(103,232,249,0.4);"
          >02</div>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-[#67e8f9] mb-2">Recall · like the prefrontal cortex</span>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Your AI gets structured context, not raw files. And only the relevant synapses.</h3>
          <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed">
            When you open Claude, Cursor, or Zed, Graphnosis surfaces a small, ranked subgraph — only the nodes relevant to your current prompt. The AI receives structured knowledge it can act on consistently, not a document it has to reparse. Hard caps: 50 nodes, 8,000 tokens. Every recall is logged.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- Step 3: Gating -->
        <article class="relative flex flex-col items-center lg:items-start text-center lg:text-left">
          <div
            class="relative z-10 w-12 h-12 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-black text-[#13131a] mb-6"
            style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #67e8f9 0%, #a78bfa 100%); box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(103,232,249,0.4);"
          >03</div>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-[#67e8f9] mb-2">Gating · like the amygdala</span>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">You decide what each AI sees. From relaxed sharing to personal sensitivity.</h3>
          <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed">
            Mark an engram Personal, Public, or Sensitive. Sensitive graphs expose at most 5 facts per recall. The gate is enforced at retrieval time — not by trust, by design. Your health notes, financial records, and private correspondence stay private even if a tool asks for them.
          </p>
          <a href="/guides/graphs-and-tiers" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-[#67e8f9] hover:underline font-mono mt-1">
            Sensitivity tiers ↗
          </a>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Stats strip -->
    <div class="mt-16 border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-3 divide-x divide-[#2a2a3d]">
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-8 px-4 text-center">
          <span class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-[#67e8f9]">~75ms</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] mt-2 leading-snug">median recall (warm)<br />single engram · local hybrid · dev hardware<br />(12,199-node benchmark corpus)</span>
        </div>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/nehloo/Graphnosis/blob/main/benchmarks/benchmarks.md"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-8 px-4 text-center transition-opacity hover:opacity-80"
          title="See the full benchmarks methodology + raw results on GitHub"
        >
          <span class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-[#a78bfa]">76.40%</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] mt-2 leading-snug">LongMemEval with GPT-4o<br />41.6% fully on-device ↗</span>
        </a>
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-8 px-4 text-center">
          <span class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-[#67e8f9]">$0</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] mt-2 leading-snug">cost to build<br />the knowledge graph</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
